        "text": " The question “is it worth it” is pretty hard to answer. There can be different assessments of the cost of LLVM being such a big project, and there are debates about how much the optimizations in LLVM matter, compared to a smaller compiler (see the discussion around Daniel Bernstein’s “the death of optimizing compilers”).\n\nThroat clearing done, Bernstein is wrong, and the answer is “yes, it’s worth it.”",
